<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; color:#000000; bEditID:r3st1; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div><div><font face="arial">Hey Youth Board!</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">Sorry for any confusion, there was no meeting tonight, please accept our apologies for the technical error with eventbright.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">We want to let you know about a fantastic opportunity open to you this summer to COME BACK AND VOLUNTEER ON NCS!</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">We are looking for inspiring members of the youth board to come and volunteer for the last week of the NCS programme. If you are interested please apply here:</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">http://survey.clicktools.com/app/survey/response.jsp</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial"><b>What’s in it for you?</b></font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">· Experience NCS from a different perspective: as part of the staff team!</font></div><div><font face="arial">· &nbsp;Develop skills to enhance your record of achievement / CV / UCAS application</font></div><div><font face="arial">· &nbsp;Attend specialist training on being a volunteer, youth work, and leadership</font></div><div><font face="arial">· Receive 1:1 support from one of our NCS managers, who can also be a reference for any future applications you do once you have completed your placement</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial"><b>What are we looking for in an Associate Mentor?</b></font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">· Reliability: Can you commit to at least four days in a row this summer? You can choose exactly when and where this would be!</font></div><div><font face="arial">· &nbsp;Professionalism: Can you be a role model for current NCS particpants, and work as part of our staff team?</font></div><div><font face="arial">· Positivity: Can you use your NCS experiences to motivate others?</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">· &nbsp; &nbsp;All applicants must attend Associate Mentor training on 31st May</font></div><div><font face="arial">· &nbsp; &nbsp; If successful, your role will last for a minimum of four days during July or August 2016 (details will be confirmed once you have been to training)</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">If you are interested please apply!</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial"><b>Finally a quick reminder of the timeline of your event from Amy:</b></font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">May- I will ensure older people are being invited to your event during this month as I know you are super busy! In the last meeting your youth board colleagues drew up a comprehensive list of people we need to invite.</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">June 22nd- Youth board will meet (times TBC) and focus on getting resources</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">July 3rd- Youth Board will visit local care homes and older people to invite them to the event personally</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">July 20th- Final Youth Board meeting before event (all need to attend!!)</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">July 23rd- Event from 1:30pm!</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">Email us at tcs.bucksandberks@the-challenge.org if you have any questions!</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">Best of luck with your revision and exams!</font></div></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 12px; border-spacing: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><tbody><tr><td style="margin: 0px;"><br></td></tr><tr><td style="font-family: arial, sans-serif; margin: 0px;"><br></td></tr><tr><td style="font-family: arial, sans-serif; margin: 0px;"><br></td></tr><tr><td align="left" height="10" valign="top" width="100%" style="font-family: arial, sans-serif; margin: 0px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(35, 31, 32);"><br></td></tr><tr><td style="font-family: arial, sans-serif; margin: 0px;"><br></td></tr><tr><td style="font-family: arial, sans-serif; margin: 0px;"><br></td></tr><tr><td align="left" height="5" valign="top" width="100%" style="font-family: arial, sans-serif; margin: 0px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(212, 41, 29);"><br></td></tr><tr><td style="font-family: arial, sans-serif; margin: 0px;"><br></td></tr><tr><td style="font-family: arial, sans-serif; margin: 0px;"><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; border-spacing: 0px;"><tbody></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></div>]]></td>
